@baude and I were chatting on IRC.  We've a reproducer that happens with `podman build` or `buildah bud`.  The interesting part is both `buildah rmi -a` and `podman rmi -a` have the same error message.  However if you do `podman rmi -a --force` it still fails while `buildah rmi -a --force` cleans everything out.

I think the error as is is correct, however `podman rmi -a --force` should remove the image(s) as Buildah does.

If @baude has other stuff to have fun with, I can look at this.
